{center}
{subhead}Microsoft Calls It Quits{def}
{left}
{p} {p}
In a move to astound the entire civilized world, Bill Gates and
Microsoft have at last admitted to years of wrong doing, monopolistic
practices, and a plot to stifle such competing technologies as Java,
Apple, and the fabled Amiga.
{p} {p}
In a resolution reached with the courts, Gates has agreed to dissolve
Microsoft into the several different companies which it had originally
taken over, and to further pay back the other companies it has
victimized, including rebates to Linux users, 500 million dollars to
Apple, and 300 million dollars to the current owners of the Amiga.
{p} {p}
